headline: Chevron Is Boosting Its Commitment to Support This Key Energy Transfer Project
summary: Chevron is taking incremental LNG volumes from Energy Transfer's proposed Lake Charles LNG project.  The company hopes to approve Lake Charles LNG by the end of this year.  Energy Transfer (NYSE: ET) has spent the better part of the past decade working to turn its Lake Charles facility from a natural gas import terminal to a liquefied natural gas (LNG) export facility.
